Hi,

I have a a root file [(uploaded to Dropbox)](https://www.dropbox.com/s/usc2nxxcbfiz22q/misalignMatrices-SensorsOnly-100.root?dl=0), that doesn't have a TTree or TBranches but instead contains a `std::map<TString, TGeoHMatrix>`. I wrote it in a C macro with this code:

```c
std::map<std::string, TGeoHMatrix> matrices;

[... fill the map here ...]

TFile *misalignmentMatrixRootfile = new TFile((misMatFileName).c_str(), "NEW");
	if (misalignmentMatrixRootfile->IsOpen()) {
		gDirectory->WriteObject(&matrices, "PndLmdMisalignMatrices");
		misalignmentMatrixRootfile->Write();
		misalignmentMatrixRootfile->Close();
	}
```

When I try to read this file with uproot, I cannot access the "PndLmdMisalignMatrices" key, instead I get a TypeError:

> TypeError: unsupported operand type(s) for -: 'NoneType' and 'int'

This is the code to read the root file:

```python
#!/usr/bin/env python3

import uproot, sys, os
import numpy as np

def readMatrices():
    matrixFile = uproot.open('./misalignMatrices-SensorsOnly-100.root')
    print(matrixFile.keys())
    matrices = matrixFile[b'PndLmdMisalignMatrices']
    print(matrices)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    readMatrices()
```

Am I reading the file a wrong way, or is this supposed to work like that? Thanks in advance!

I'm saving a few `std::string`s as single entry branches as meta data in a tree. To retrieve that data I'm trying to just use the structure:
```
>>> meta_info_str = uproot.open('file.root')['tree'].array('meta')[0]
```
Where `meta` is an `std::string` branch.

I'm getting the `ValueError`:
```
cannot interpret branch b'meta' as a Python type
```

 They are saved in C++ as follows:

```cpp
/// header .. define class member
TTree* m_tree;
std::string m_some_meta_string;
```
```cpp
/// in source .. set the branch
m_tree = new TTree("tree","tree");
m_tree->Branch("meta",&m_some_meta_string);
/// later assign it
m_some_meta_string = function_which_returns_a_string();
```

An example file can be found here: https://phy.duke.edu/~ddavis/public/example.root
The tree with some strings is called `WtLoop_meta`. String branches include `generator`, `sampleType`, `campaign`, and `initialState`. If I use `tree.show()` I see a `None` interpretation for the strings.

Docs say that `uproot` should be able to figure out `std::string`, am I screwing something up (e.g. saving the string to the ROOT file in a way that's incompatible with `uproot`)?

Using ROOT v6-10-08 to create the file and uproot v2.8.8 to read.

It seems that the remaining issue in #28 was caused by a char* field in an object. Example ROOT file and code attached. The issue is with the streamer for the `name` field in the `mydata` class.

[test.root.gz](https://github.com/scikit-hep/uproot/files/1533311/test.root.gz)

```
#include "TFile.h"
#include "TTree.h"

class mydata : public TObject {
    public:
        mydata() { };
        virtual ~mydata() { };

        int size;
        char* name;
        void set(const char* n, int s) {
                size = s;
                name = new char[s];
                strncpy(name,n,s);
        }

        ClassDef(mydata, 1);
};

void test_uproot()
{
  TFile file("test.root","RECREATE");
  TTree tree("T","T");

  mydata data;

  tree.Branch("data",&data);

  for (int i = 0; i < 1; i++) {
    data.set("test",4);
    tree.Fill();
  }

  tree.Write();

  file.Write();
  file.Close();
}
```

